Dock like this is a standard for every geek. It is almost
unimaginable to run graphical session without a widget that
will provide CPU, memory, disk, net, battery and other
informations in any place and any time.

Gkrellm is themed application. in Gkrellm directory, there
is NsCDE theme with changable color scheme (from palette).
Provided example script colormgr.local.example can be put
in $FVWM_USERDIR/libexec as "colormgr.local" and routines
in it will set "NsCDE" theme in $HOME/.gkrellm2/themes/NsCDE
Script colormgr.local is run from Color Style Manager on
theme apply if it exists and if it is executable.
